public static Man getMaxAgeMan(List<Man> list) {
    Iterator<Man> iterator = list.iterator();
    Man maxAgeMan = iterator.next();
    while (iterator.hasNext()) {
        Man man = iterator.next();
        if (man.getAge() > maxAgeMan.getAge()) {
            maxAgeMan = man;
        }
    }
    return maxAgeMan;
}
<<<explanation>>>:
This method uses an iterator to iterate through the list of Man objects. It starts by calling the next() method on the iterator to get the first Man object in the list. This Man object is then assigned to the maxAgeMan variable.
The while loop then checks if there are more Man objects in the list by calling the hasNext() method on the iterator. If there are more Man objects, the next() method is called on the iterator to get the next Man object in the list.
The age of the current Man object is compared to the age of the maxAgeMan variable. If the current Man object is older than the maxAgeMan variable, the current Man object is assigned to the maxAgeMan variable.
After the while loop has finished iterating through the list of Man objects, the maxAgeMan variable will contain the Man object with the highest age.
